<subSubSection id="C7573400928155EA4186177731637206" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4DDFDA76F26EF89089672D235F8E6FA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="536F80B756BCF2787B727FB79C5885D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species was adequately described by 
<bibRefCitation id="1BCC6BE62A9472632F1E2F7DC845DE8A" author="Bezzi, M" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Indian Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="53 - 175" refId="B2" refString="Bezzi, M, 1913. Indian trypaneids (fruit-flies) in the collection of the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 3: 53 - 175" title="Indian trypaneids (fruit-flies) in the collection of the Indian Museum, Calcutta." volume="3" year="1913">Bezzi (1913)</bibRefCitation>
except for the postabdominal structures. It is almost inseparable from 
<taxonomicName id="38A300A0DDEDA4D2141ABD4ADE2669FF" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. platyptera" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="457A9BC1B616C5FC0D97460240A2F101" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except for the presence of only basal scutellar setae instead of both apical and basal setae as in 
<taxonomicName id="0A16E50B24BF2AD631704F947D59C12B" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. platyptera" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="4F28EBAE6A6138E746D10A4B01C698AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="42BC86D275058A9BFF83128890430FFE" captionStart="Figures 42–43" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 42 - 43. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 42 habitus (dorsal) 43 habitus (lateral)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures42-43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669206" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">42</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A857BDCAE304A1F24BD23F635D312958" captionStart="Figures 42–43" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 42 - 43. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 42 habitus (dorsal) 43 habitus (lateral)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures42-43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669206" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
