<subSubSection id="9C1D5176F9069A4FD724DFE84AA5C423" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="male genitalia">
<paragraph id="4618927D38C5C48F5FEDDBC72E1ADFDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Male genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA60567890EE84AD44024791E1086937" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Epandrium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EDA4000FAF8375DDBEBC195AE7C02B18" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">44</figureCitation>
) brown, sclerotised, with no demarcation from lateral surstylus (in profile view); epandrium and surstyli oval in posterior view, with well-developed prensisetae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E126C9B73492AE293ADABE62F91AD33D" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">45</figureCitation>
). Phallus 1.39 mm long including glans; glans stout, with broad sclerotised rod (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="53250A1ACF2DC2ED1BEBAED74E662B61" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">46</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="68A157140156D73F51157044947387B2" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figures 44–51" startId="F11">
<paragraph id="917A227BE4A7FFB93C1456C6342C5298" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="84A12B813F5E1A443A93A912B4D19DA7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Figures 44-51.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6B73135A3AB285CDFAF1B65F601360D1" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Platensina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platensina zodiacalis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zodiacalis">
<emphasis id="1C623F99252D4CC8B2E3B438CB7D836F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Platensina zodiacalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bezzi) 
<emphasis id="0DC35BD6AFAAA864B74C7A59DE4DC3FC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">44</emphasis>
epandrium (lateral) 
<emphasis id="0E5AAA9DB6DDC66DB36AFEC8BA1CCD91" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">45</emphasis>
epandrium (posterior view) 
<emphasis id="43F850BF54DC4A1A151A7DB0837B0FA0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">46</emphasis>
glans of phallus 
<emphasis id="DA2C38CF4957ABA8520D7C8B35EC8E7C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">47</emphasis>
ovipositor 
<emphasis id="DC3714DEFE2A60F76FDBCDAFA320F44F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">48</emphasis>
