<subSubSection id="FF8ED28FDFCEA119C610457854319690" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="female genitalia">
<paragraph id="2BED9F538B01995F5288579A3B082956" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Female genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E7DA3DCE6D7E18AC2967AF9CD3E3D05" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Oviscape 0.92 mm long, dark brown, conical, dorsoventrally flattened (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="926E92423F3F825FDAB879B4F4B0D891" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">47</figureCitation>
); eversible membrane 0.72 mm long, shorter than oviscape, with conical spicules along entire length except for a few rows of flattened ones distally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6963CC3C8D4DAE3C41BD597BD94D2862" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">48</figureCitation>
); taeniae short, dark brown, 0.25 length of eversible membrane. Aculeus shorter than eversible membrane, 0.63 mm long, dorsoventrally flattened; apex of aculeus rounded (Figs 
<figureCitation id="9BFCEA5CC88093D22345D6BD8A392C1F" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">50</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FCA1C35AE09C915A83C221B968171A67" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">51</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca brown, club-shaped, with numerous papillae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92DD2A9A6586B931490424B6F38E4885" captionStart="Figures 44–51" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 44 - 51. Platensina zodiacalis (Bezzi) 44 epandrium (lateral) 45 epandrium (posterior view) 46 glans of phallus 47 ovipositor 48 spicules on eversible membrane 49 spermatheca 50 aculeus 51 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures44-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669207" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F9069F4B57EC0517919080CC2C67546D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F1132FBD7A9E4975345FDD281ED90799" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8C8E6DFC1E4F66429B81AA095E4E99E" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is widespread from India (Karnataka, Assam) and Sri Lanka to southern China and Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="C0AC33F02B47F86B2D467C052AD3C177" author="Hancock, DL" journalOrPublisher="Australian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="305 - 320" refId="B9" refString="Hancock, DL, 2012. Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya. Australian Entomologist 39 (4): 305 - 320" title="Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya." volume="39" year="2012">Hancock 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
